# HEADLESS PRIMITIVES PROPS API RULESET
**(Strict Prop Rules + WHY/WHEN/HOW + Applicability Rule – Zero Interpretation Allowed – Research-Backed March 3, 2026)**

**0. GLOBAL ENFORCEMENT**  
1. All generated primitives MUST follow this document exactly.  
2. Any violation = immediate rejection and full regeneration.  
3. This ruleset applies to every primitive in the library.  
4. The API MUST exactly match Radix UI primitives (dominant standard). React Aria naming is FORBIDDEN.

**PROP APPLICABILITY RULE (ZERO GUESSING ALLOWED)**  
- Include a prop ONLY if it is required by the exact official Radix UI primitive of the same name (latest stable version).  
- Never add or guess extra props.

**1. CORE PROPS (HARD RULES – ONE PER PROP WITH WHY/WHEN/HOW)**  
(These must be implemented exactly where the Radix primitive of the same name uses them.)

1. **open?** (boolean | undefined)  
   - WHY: Enables controlled mode for WCAG focus/ARIA.  
   - WHEN: Every openable primitive (Dialog, Popover, DropdownMenu, etc.).  
   - HOW: Controlled when provided; call onOpenChange on every change.

2. **defaultOpen?** (boolean)  
   - WHY: Uncontrolled initial state.  
   - WHEN: With open.  
   - HOW: Ignored if open present. Default = false.

3. **onOpenChange?** ((open: boolean) => void)  
   - WHY: Consumer notification.  
   - WHEN: With open/defaultOpen.  
   - HOW: Called with new value every time.

4. **value?** (any)  
   - WHY: Controlled selection.  
   - WHEN: Tabs, Select, RadioGroup, ToggleGroup, etc.  
   - HOW: Controlled when provided.

5. **defaultValue?** (any)  
   - WHY: Uncontrolled initial value.  
   - WHEN: With value.  
   - HOW: Ignored if value present.

6. **onValueChange?** ((value: any) => void)  
   - WHY: Consumer notification.  
   - WHEN: With value/defaultValue.  
   - HOW: Called with new value.

7. **checked?** (boolean | undefined)  
   - WHY: Controlled boolean state.  
   - WHEN: Checkbox, Switch, Toggle.  
   - HOW: Controlled when provided.

8. **defaultChecked?** (boolean)  
   - WHY: Uncontrolled initial checked.  
   - WHEN: With checked.  
   - HOW: Ignored if checked present.

9. **onCheckedChange?** ((checked: boolean) => void)  
   - WHY: Consumer notification.  
   - WHEN: With checked/defaultChecked.  
   - HOW: Called with new value.

10. **disabled?** (boolean)  
    - WHY: Prevents interaction + correct ARIA.  
    - WHEN: EVERY interactive primitive.  
    - HOW: Skip focus/events, aria-disabled="true". Default = false.

11. **asChild** (boolean)  
    - WHY: Polymorphic rendering.  
    - WHEN: EVERY root primitive.  
    - HOW: Default = false. When true: React.cloneElement on single child.

12. **ref** (via React.forwardRef)  
    - WHY: DOM access for focus/testing.  
    - WHEN: EVERY primitive.  
    - HOW: Forward to root (or child when asChild).

13. **...props**  
    - WHY: Full HTML/ARIA forwarding.  
    - WHEN: EVERY primitive.  
    - HOW: Spread all remaining attributes unchanged.

14. **id?** (string)  
    - WHY: ARIA linking.  
    - WHEN: EVERY primitive.  
    - HOW: Auto-generate with React.useId() if missing.

**2. EXPORT RULE (MANDATORY)**  
- EVERY primitive MUST export a TypeScript interface named exactly `ComponentNameProps` (e.g. `DialogProps`, `SelectProps`).  
- The component MUST be typed with this interface: `React.forwardRef<ComponentNameProps, ...>`.

**3. COMPONENT-SPECIFIC PROPS (ALLOWED ONLY)**  
Extra props are permitted **only** if they exist in the official Radix UI primitive of the exact same name (latest stable).  
Examples (not exhaustive): modal, forceMount, side, align, loop, collapsible, required, name, onSelect, placeholder, etc.  
They MUST be documented with the same WHY/WHEN/HOW style internally.

**4. FORBIDDEN PROPS (HARD RULES)**  
- className, style, css, variant, size, color or any visual prop  
- isOpen, isChecked, isSelected, isDisabled, render (React Aria naming)  
- selected? (never use as top-level prop)  
- Any prop not present in the real Radix primitive of the same name

**REJECTION CONDITION**  
Any code that breaks any rule above (including guessing extra props or omitting the ComponentNameProps interface) MUST be rejected and regenerated until perfect.